amily:Arial; font-size:11pt">is</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">still</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">clearly</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">much</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">for</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">PCCs</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">do</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">prove</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">their</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">worth</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">public,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">he</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">outcome</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">of</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">this</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">inquiry</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">should</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">therefore</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">be</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">seen</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">as</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">progress</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">report</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">rather</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">than</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">definitive</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">statement</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">on</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">success</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">of</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">model.</span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Police</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Foundation</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">December 2013</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt; text-align:right"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">8</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> For example, a report from the Revolving Doors Agency (Revolving Doors Agency (2013) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">First Generation: One Year On</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> – available at </span><a href="http://www.revolving-doors.org.uk/documents/first-generation-one-year-on/"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.revolving-doors.org.uk/documents/first-generation-one-year-on/</span></a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">) welcomes efforts by some PCCs to seek “lasting systemic change through partnership” with a view to reducing crime and improving wellbeing in their areas.</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn2"></a><a href="#_ftnref2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> For example, a recent opinion poll found that 64% of people think that PCCs have made no difference to the police’s effectiveness at combating crime (3% thought PCCs had made the police more effective, 9% less effective and 25% did not know). Poll results available at </span><a href="http://d25d2506sfb94s.cloudfront.net/cumulus_uploads/document/jwnzb06i31/YG-Archive-131112-TimesPCCs.pdf"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://d25d2506sfb94s.cloudfront.net/cumulus_uploads/document/jwnzb06i31/YG-Archive-131112-TimesPCCs.pdf</span></a></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn3"></a><a href="#_ftnref3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> p.82: Independent Police Commission (2013) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">Policing for a Better Britain: Report of the Independent Police Commission</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> – available at </span><a href="http://independentpolicecommission.org.uk/uploads/37d80308-be23-9684-054d-e4958bb9d518.pdf"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://independentpolicecommission.org.uk/uploads/37d80308-be23-9684-054d-e4958bb9d518.pdf</span></a></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn4"></a><a href="#_ftnref4">[4]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> House of Commons Home Affairs Committee (2013) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">Police and Crime Commissioners: Power to remove Chief Constables,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> Sixth Report of Session 2013-14, London: The Stationery Office Limited.</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn5"></a><a href="#_ftnref5">[5]</a><a href="http://www.police-foundation.org.uk/news/93/22/Tom-Winsor-gives-the-Foundation-s-John-Harris-Lecture/d,News-main"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.police-foundation.org.uk/news/93/22/Tom-Winsor-gives-the-Foundation-s-John-Harris-Lecture/d,News-main</span></a></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn6"></a><a href="#_ftnref6">[6]</a><a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-24148129"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-24148129</span></a></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn7"></a><a href="#_ftnref7">[7]</a><a href="http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2516121/Crackdown-police-chiefs-luxury-cars-tax-break.html"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2516121/Crackdown-police-chiefs-luxury-cars-tax-break.html</span></a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> and see for example </span><a href="http://www.northyorkshire-pcc.gov.uk/taking-action/making-decisions/decisions-made/0812013-review-of-chief-police-officer-remuneration-terms-and-conditions/"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.northyorkshire-pcc.gov.uk/taking-action/making-decisions/decisions-made/0812013-review-of-chief-police-officer-remuneration-terms-and-conditions/</span></a></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn8"></a><a href="#_ftnref8">[8]</a><a href="http://www.thamesvalley-pcc.gov.uk/Document-Library/Letter-to-council-leaders-11-11-13.pdf"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.thamesvalley-pcc.gov.uk/Document-Library/Letter-to-council-leaders-11-11-13.pdf</span></a></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn9"></a><a href="#_ftnref9">[9]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> At present, at least one PCP (in West Yorkshire) receives additional funding from local sources while others rely solely on the funding provided by the Home Office.</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn10"></a><a href="#_ftnref10">[10]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> See, for example, </span><a href="http://www.westmidlands-pcc.gov.uk/consultation/budget-and-precept-2014-15"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.westmidlands-pcc.gov.uk/consultation/budget-and-precept-2014-15</span></a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> and </span><a href="http://www.sussex-pcc.gov.uk/precept-consultation/"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.sussex-pcc.gov.uk/precept-consultation/</span></a></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn11"></a><a href="#_ftnref11">[11]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> Poll results available at </span><a href="http://thecentreground.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/Centreground-Results-131108-Police-RESULTS.pdf"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://thecentreground.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/Centreground-Results-131108-Police-RESULTS.pdf</span></a></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn12"></a><a href="#_ftnref12">[12]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> Their annual report on police funding stated that: </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">“HMIC is deeply disappointed with progress on collaboration … the pace of change on collaboration is too slow”</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">HMIC (2013) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">Policing in Austerity: Rising to the Challenge,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> London: HMIC</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn13"></a><a href="#_ftnref13">[13]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Gilmore, M. (2013) ‘Police and Crime Commissioners One Year On’ in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">The RUSI Journal,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> 158: 5, p.48-55.</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn14"></a><a href="#_ftnref14">[14]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> For example, five forces in the South West of England have agreed to pursue a new regional forensic services collaboration (</span><a href="http://www.avonandsomerset-pcc.gov.uk/News-and-Events/News-Archive/2013/November/South-West-Forces-agree-Regional-Forensic-Collaboration.aspx"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.avonandsomerset-pcc.gov.uk/News-and-Events/News-Archive/2013/November/South-West-Forces-agree-Regional-Forensic-Collaboration.aspx</span></a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">), while collaboration between Sussex and Surrey police forces was extended from 1</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:6.67pt; vertical-align:super">st</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> October 2013.</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn15"></a><a href="#_ftnref15">[15]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> This was recently recognised in a collaboration agreement between Bedfordshire, Cambridgeshire and Hertfordshire – for details see </span><a href="http://www.bedfordshire.pcc.police.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/105-Collaboration-expansion-Dec-13.pdf"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.bedfordshire.pcc.police.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/105-Collaboration-expansion-Dec-13.pdf</span></a></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn16"></a><a href="#_ftnref16">[16]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Gilmore, M. (2013) ‘Police and Crime Commissioners One Year On’ in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">The RUSI Journal,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> 158: 5, p.48-55.</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn17"></a><a href="#_ftnref17">[17]</a><a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-22624096"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-22624096</span></a></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn18"></a><a href="#_ftnref18">[18]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> House of Commons Home Affairs Committee (2013) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">Police and Crime Commissioners: Register of Interests,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> First Report of Session 2013-14, London: The Stationery Office Limited.</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn19"></a><a href="#_ftnref19">[19]</a><a href="http://copacc.files.wordpress.com/2013/10/copacc-pcc-statutory-transparency-thematic-nov2013-vopen.pdf"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://copacc.files.wordpress.com/2013/10/copacc-pcc-statutory-transparency-thematic-nov2013-vopen.pdf</span></a></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn20"></a><a href="#_ftnref20">[20]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> For example, Chris Salmon, PCC for Dyfed-Powys, recently reported his office ‘receives in a day what the former police authority used to receive in a month’ (Salmon, C. (2013) ‘Opening the castle gates: how PCCs can deliver the public’s priorities’ in Chambers, M. (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">ed</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">The Pioneers: Police and Crime Commissioners, one year on</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">, London: Policy Exchange)</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn21"></a><a href="#_ftnref21">[21]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Further: 46% did not agree, 26% neither agreed nor disagreed and 11% did not know. Poll results available at </span><a href="http://thecentreground.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/Centreground-Results-131108-Police-RESULTS.pdf"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://thecentreground.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/Centreground-Results-131108-Police-RESULTS.pdf</span></a></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn22"></a><a href="#_ftnref22">[22]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> Poll results available at </span><a href="http://www.comres.co.uk/poll/1031/bbc-police-and-crime-commissioner-study.htm"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.comres.co.uk/poll/1031/bbc-police-and-crime-commissioner-study.htm</span></a></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn23"></a><a href="#_ftnref23">[23]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> Quoted in Gilmore, M. (2013) ‘Police and Crime Commissioners One Year On’ in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">The RUSI Journal,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> 158: 5, p.48-55.</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn24"></a><a href="#_ftnref24">[24]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> Home Secretary’s speech ‘Police and Crime Commissioners, one year on: warts and all’, delivered on 13 November 2013 and available at </span><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/speeches/police-and-crime-commissioners-one-year-on-warts-and-all"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">https://www.gov.uk/government/speeches/police-and-crime-commissioners-one-year-on-warts-and-all</span></a></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn25"></a><a href="#_ftnref25">[25]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> p.27: Mulligan, J. (2013) ‘Cutting Crime’ in Chambers, M. (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">ed</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">The Pioneers: Police and Crime Commissioners, one year on</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">, London: Policy Exchange.</span></p></body></html>